==English==
===Etymology===
French, "long chair", from French ''[[chaise]]'' ("[[chair]]") + ''[[longue]]'' ("[[long]]")
===Noun===
'''chaise longue''', pl. ''[[chaise longues]]'' or ''[[chaises longues]]''
#a reclining chair with a long seat, which can support the outstretched legs of a sitter.

